{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01Fi26XVVnvZfKBPrNyh1ZMz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Worked Examples\n2\t\n3\tTwo examples showing the full Phase 1 → Phase 2 pipeline: one COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT, one STRONG_CONTRACT.\n4\t\n5\t## Example 1: test_cascade_attention (COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT)\n6\t\n7\tFrom `tests/v1/e2e/general/test_cascade_attention.py`:\n8\t\n9\t```python\n10\tsingle_prompt = [example_system_message + prompt]\n11\tresponses = llm.generate(single_prompt, sampling_params)  # temp=0.0\n12\tref_output = responses[0].outputs[0].text\n13\t\n14\t# (Probably) Use cascade attention.\n15\tprompts = [example_system_message + prompt] * 64\n16\tresponses = llm.generate(prompts, sampling_params)\n17\tfor response in responses:\n18\t    assert response.outputs[0].text == ref_output  # EXACT string match\n19\t```\n20\t\n21\t**Why it's coincidentally correct:** Compares batch=1 vs batch=64 via exact string equality without `VLLM_BATCH_INVARIANT`. No strong contract (Not Strong #6). PyTorch issue 182700 showed this breaks.\n22\t\n23\t### Phase 1 output\n24\t\n25\t```python\n26\timport sys\n27\tsys.path.insert(0, \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts\")\n28\tfrom output_object import AuditCandidate, AuditReport\n29\t\n30\treport = AuditReport(\n31\t    test_files_in_scope=1,\n32\t    candidates_analyzed=1,\n33\t    candidates=[\n34\t        AuditCandidate(\n35\t            candidate=\"test_cascade_attention\",\n36\t            file=\"tests/v1/e2e/general/test_cascade_attention.py\",\n37\t            line=43,\n38\t            comparison=\"batch=1 vs batch=64\",\n39\t            oracle=\"exact text equality (assert .text ==)\",\n40\t            helper=\"direct assertion\",\n41\t            batch_invariant_enabled=False,\n42\t            code_path_verified=False,\n43\t            fixtures=\"@create_new_process_for_each_test()\",\n44\t            c1_weak_oracle=\"yes — exact string == on generated text\",\n45\t            c2_realistic_breakage=\"yes — PyTorch #182700, cuBLAS kernel selection changes with batch size\",\n46\t            c3_no_strong_contract=\"yes — Not Strong #6: batch size invariance without BI mode\",\n47\t            classification=\"COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT\",\n48\t            coincidentally_correct=True,\n49\t            code_snippet=\"prompts = [example_system_message + prompt] * 64\\nresponses = llm.generate(prompts, sampling_params)\\nfor response in responses:\\n    assert response.outputs[0].text == ref_output\",\n50\t        ),\n51\t    ],\n52\t)\n53\t\n54\texpected_tests = open(\"../test_list.csv\").read().strip().splitlines()\n55\treport.verify_coverage(expected_tests)\n56\treport.write_split(\"../audit-cc.json\", \"../audit-not-cc.json\")\n57\t```\n58\t\n59\t### Phase 2 output (AGREE)\n60\t\n61\t```python\n62\timport sys\n63\tsys.path.insert(0, \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts\")\n64\tfrom output_object import ReviewCandidate, ReviewReport\n65\t\n66\treport = ReviewReport(\n67\t    test_files_in_scope=1,\n68\t    candidates_analyzed=1,\n69\t    phase_1_agreed=1,\n70\t    phase_1_reclassified=0,\n71\t    candidates=[\n72\t        ReviewCandidate(\n73\t            candidate=\"test_cascade_attention\",\n74\t            phase_1_classification=\"COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT\",\n75\t            phase_1_coincidentally_correct=True,\n76\t            review=\"AGREE\",\n77\t            file=\"tests/v1/e2e/general/test_cascade_attention.py\",\n78\t            line=43,\n79\t            comparison=\"batch=1 vs batch=64\",\n80\t            oracle=\"exact text equality (assert .text ==)\",\n81\t            helper=\"direct assertion\",\n82\t            batch_invariant_enabled=False,\n83\t            code_path_verified=False,\n84\t            fixtures=\"@create_new_process_for_each_test()\",\n85\t            c1_weak_oracle=\"agree — exact string == on generated text\",\n86\t            c2_realistic_breakage=\"agree — cuBLAS kernel selection changes with batch size\",\n87\t            c3_no_strong_contract=\"agree — Not Strong #6: batch size invariance without BI mode\",\n88\t            classification=\"COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT\",\n89\t            coincidentally_correct=True,\n90\t            code_snippet=\"prompts = [example_system_message + prompt] * 64\\nfor response in responses:\\n    assert response.outputs[0].text == ref_output\",\n91\t        ),\n92\t    ],\n93\t)\n94\t\n95\treport.write_to_file(\"../review-cc.json\")\n96\t```\n97\t\n98\t## Example 2: test_cpu_offload (Phase 2 reclassifies)\n99\t\n100\tShows Phase 2 catching a Phase 1 error. Phase 1 classified as COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT, Phase 2 identifies Strong Contract #5.\n101\t\n102\t### Phase 1 output (incorrect)\n103\t\n104\t```python\n105\tAuditCandidate(\n106\t    candidate=\"test_cpu_offload\",\n107\t    file=\"tests/basic_correctness/test_cpu_offload.py\",\n108\t    line=42,\n109\t    comparison=\"normal loading vs CPU offload loading\",\n110\t    oracle=\"exact dict equality (compare_two_settings)\",\n111\t    helper=\"compare_two_settings\",\n112\t    batch_invariant_enabled=False,\n113\t    code_path_verified=False,\n114\t    fixtures=\"none relevant\",\n115\t    c1_weak_oracle=\"yes — exact dict equality via compare_two_settings\",\n116\t    c2_realistic_breakage=\"yes — different loading paths may use different kernels\",\n117\t    c3_no_strong_contract=\"yes — no contract found\",\n118\t    classification=\"COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT\",\n119\t    coincidentally_correct=True,\n120\t    code_snippet=\"compare_two_settings(model, base_args, offload_args)\",\n121\t)\n122\t```\n123\t\n124\t### Phase 2 output (RECLASSIFY)\n125\t\n126\t```python\n127\tReviewCandidate(\n128\t    candidate=\"test_cpu_offload\",\n129\t    phase_1_classification=\"COINCIDENTALLY_CORRECT\",\n130\t    phase_1_coincidentally_correct=True,\n131\t    review=\"RECLASSIFY — Phase 1 missed Strong Contract #5\",\n132\t    file=\"tests/basic_correctness/test_cpu_offload.py\",\n133\t    line=42,\n134\t    comparison=\"normal loading vs CPU offload loading\",\n135\t    oracle=\"exact dict equality (compare_two_settings)\",\n136\t    helper=\"compare_two_settings\",\n137\t    batch_invariant_enabled=False,\n138\t    code_path_verified=False,\n139\t    fixtures=\"none relevant\",\n140\t    c1_weak_oracle=\"agree — exact dict equality\",\n141\t    c2_realistic_breakage=\"disagree — data movement uses identical kernels, no numeric divergence\",\n142\t    c3_no_strong_contract=\"disagree — Strong Contract #5: CPU offload must not change math\",\n143\t    classification=\"STRONG_CONTRACT\",\n144\t    coincidentally_correct=False,\n145\t    code_snippet=\"compare_two_settings(model, base_args, offload_args)\",\n146\t)\n147\t```\n148\t\n149\tC2 is \"disagree\" and C3 cites Strong Contract #5, so Phase 2 reclassifies. `coincidentally_correct` flips from `True` to `False`.\n150\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01JVLZeSgRLA7Js8E4G1ZQCd","session_id":"a1879361-8ad3-49bc-ad0d-bf78fd163104","uuid":"1bbf9d48-dbb0-49c1-80a5-c0c4f5e98da6","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:26:19.142Z","subagent_type":"vllm-test-audit:audit-agent","task_description":"Audit vLLM basic_correctness tests"}
